<paragraph pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="64" pageNumber="65">
This is likely an undescribed species from the lower end of evergreen forests in southeastern Toliara Province. The pistillate flowers have a very long pedicel, and the calyx is very well developed. It is likely the same as 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. nitidulus subsp. var. var. eglandulosus" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" rank="variety" species="nitidulus" subSpecies="var." variety="eglandulosus">C. nitidulus var. eglandulosus</taxonomicName>
and C. 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Croton" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Croton thouarsianus subsp. var. var. angustifolius" order="Malpighiales" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="thouarsianus" subSpecies="var." variety="angustifolius">
